Brigadier Leonard Hlathi, provincial police spokesperson, said that the Community Service Centre will now operate from the Police Station Finance Office in Beyers Naude Street, behind the The telephone lines at the Middelburg Police Station will also not be accessible at this time. The community is advised to use the following numbers for emergencies and complaints: •013 247 7000 •013 249 1685 •013 249 1688 The Middelburg Police Communication Officer, Captain Khanyisile Zwane, can be contacted on 082 462 1896. Acting Visible Policing Head, Lt. Col. Joseph Maphila can be reached on 082 462 2315. Brig. Hlathi said that the police station will be reopened on Sunday 12 July.